00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:44.080
' I believe God is a miracle-working God.

00:24:44.080 --> 00:24:45.733
I do.

00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:54.940
But the law of seedtime and harvest is: whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

00:24:59.051 --> 00:25:00.793
You can't call in a harvest of something you don't have the seed in the ground for.

00:25:00.793 --> 00:25:03.531
How can a farmer do that?

00:25:03.531 --> 00:25:17.860
If seedtime and harvest never ceases—whatever the Law of Genesis talks about when it says everything produces after its own kind—what are you sowing?

00:25:17.860 --> 00:25:23.074
A farmer goes out and puts a half-acre field out there, but he's believing for five acres.

00:25:23.074 --> 00:25:25.820
That would be real stupid, wouldn't it?

00:25:25.820 --> 00:25:39.338
'Well, I sowed it, honey, in that first acre,' but we're going to pray as a family for the whole five acres to come, even though we only planted and sowed for one.

00:25:39.338 --> 00:25:42.994
That's what a lot of the body of Christ does.

00:25:59.200 --> 00:25:59.547
I think it's sad.

00:26:15.423 --> 00:26:15.760
People perish for a lack of knowledge, but everything is produced according to law.

00:26:15.760 --> 00:26:21.214
How is it multiplication when the Bible says 30, 60, and 100-fold?

00:26:21.214 --> 00:26:23.871
'Well, I'm believing for a million-fold.

00:26:23.871 --> 00:26:27.698
' Come on, man.

00:26:27.698 --> 00:26:31.308
The Bible doesn't even say a million-fold.

00:26:31.308 --> 00:26:36.632
The Bible says a thousand-fold: some 30, some 60, and some 100-fold.

00:26:36.632 --> 00:26:49.000
You have way-out-there La-La Land faith, but if you don't have the seed to believe for that, it all goes by spiritual law.

00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:56.480
People try to give you all this pie-in-the-sky: 'Well, I'm going to get this, and it's going to happen.

00:26:56.480 --> 00:27:04.120
' I believe you can sow, and you have a right to call it in on what you sowed.

00:27:04.830 --> 00:27:07.269
The multiplication comes by what you've sowed.

00:27:07.269 --> 00:27:08.811
That's what I believe.

00:27:08.811 --> 00:27:24.666
Now, when you get the harvest of that and you believe God, you keep believing and you sow your $10 or $100—that's consistency; it adds up real quick.

00:27:32.462 --> 00:27:37.164
But people get off into weird things, and you can't even add spiritual backing behind it.

00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:40.687
All that you pray, you have to have word-backed prayers.

00:27:40.687 --> 00:27:48.160
'If you abide in Me and My words remain in you, you shall ask what you will and it shall be done.

00:27:48.160 --> 00:27:52.308
' But the Word has to back what you're praying.

00:27:57.925 --> 00:27:58.130
If you don't have word-backed prayers, it's just like saying, 'Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star.

00:27:58.130 --> 00:28:00.584
' You're not going to get anything.

00:28:00.584 --> 00:28:02.700
You must have word-backed prayers.

00:28:02.700 --> 00:28:22.096
Find scripture that pertains to what you're believing for, but make sure you're practicing what the Word said to do, because you're not going to get what the Word says you could have unless you're doing what the Word said to do.

00:28:22.096 --> 00:28:25.898
People get flaky, especially in the charismatic circles.

00:28:31.990 --> 00:28:35.265
You have to be grounded and find the Word to back what you're believing for, but then do what the Word told you to do in the first place.

00:28:35.265 --> 00:28:36.120
Stay out of sin.

00:28:36.120 --> 00:28:41.093
Faith works by love; keep love a priority in your house.

00:28:41.093 --> 00:28:41.733
Take communion.

00:28:41.733 --> 00:28:42.973
Fellowship with the Father.

00:28:42.973 --> 00:28:45.720
Sow your seeds and believe for the harvest.

00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:49.008
Now, where do you sow?

00:28:49.008 --> 00:28:50.719
You sow into good ground.

00:28:50.719 --> 00:28:56.865
'Well, I've been sowing into Brother So-and-So, and I haven't gotten anything for the last five years.

00:28:56.865 --> 00:28:58.440
' Then stop doing it.

00:28:58.440 --> 00:29:02.067
Use some wisdom.

00:29:02.067 --> 00:29:16.406
If the farmer kept planting in that ground, he's going to have to either put some fertilizer in that ground to get it to produce or something.

00:29:16.406 --> 00:29:23.627
People try to ask me these things all the time, and I think it's just common sense.

00:29:23.627 --> 00:29:27.074
If I want to sow soybeans, I don't plant corn.

00:29:27.074 --> 00:29:34.396
If I want a harvest of cotton, or maybe you wanted a really good watermelon, you don't plant cantaloupe.

00:29:34.396 --> 00:29:37.432
My mind just thinks simply about things, and I see it work.

00:29:42.213 --> 00:29:47.135
I know what law is, and I understand that a corn plant is only going to produce so much corn.

00:29:47.135 --> 00:29:52.240
So, you better plant a whole lot more if you want a whole mess of corn.

00:29:52.240 --> 00:29:54.920
For the measure that you sow, that will you reap.

00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:04.600
It's even scripture.

00:30:04.600 --> 00:30:08.900
If you sow a thimbleful, you're going to reap a thimble.

00:30:08.900 --> 00:30:15.840
If you sow a dump truck, you're going to reap dump trucks.

00:30:15.840 --> 00:30:18.400
If you sow a vineyard, you're going to reap vineyards.

00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:27.120
But people make it complicated and think, 'Well, I'm qualified, so XRP is going to make it happen for me.

00:30:27.120 --> 00:30:39.530
' And I go, 'Okay, but even if it did and you put your money into it, are you going to keep it?

00:30:39.530 --> 00:30:42.458
Will it be riches without sorrow, or will you lose it all?

00:30:42.458 --> 00:30:43.880
' 'Well, I won the lottery, brother.

00:30:43.880 --> 00:30:46.820
' But that's just a game of chance.

00:30:46.820 --> 00:30:50.063
I'm talking about walking in spiritual authority and law.

00:31:01.316 --> 00:31:01.498
I don't believe in chance.

00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:09.645
I don't play the lottery.

00:31:12.902 --> 00:31:13.164
I don't do scratch-offs.

00:31:13.164 --> 00:31:27.400
Back in the day, it was fun—every once in a while, I'd go, 'Oh yeah, they got that $5 scratch-off ticket,' and if I won something, I'd take the kids out and get an ice cream—but I don't look at games of chance.

00:31:44.180 --> 00:31:44.585
I put my hand to something, and whatever I put my hands to, the Lord blesses.

00:31:53.055 --> 00:31:53.270
I don't look for a mailbox mentality faith.

00:32:06.884 --> 00:32:07.102
I'm always looking for a miracle in the mailbox.

00:32:23.760 --> 00:32:24.160
Whatever I put my hands to will prosper.

00:32:25.192 --> 00:32:26.584
I ask God to bless my hands.

00:32:38.280 --> 00:32:38.617
I ask God to bless my mind.

00:32:38.617 --> 00:32:42.248
Show me, Lord, where to do things.

00:32:44.840 --> 00:32:53.816
And I'll be driving down the road—I kid you not, it's something we talk about all the time—and I'll be praying in the Holy Spirit.

00:32:53.816 --> 00:32:57.669
He says, "You see that land right there?

00:33:04.977 --> 00:33:05.320
It just came up for sale.

00:33:05.320 --> 00:33:11.377
" And in the natural, I know I can't buy it.

00:33:11.377 --> 00:33:13.295
I don't have it.

00:33:13.295 --> 00:33:20.126
But He's talking to me about things, stretching me, making me believe for more.

00:33:28.075 --> 00:33:28.280
And in the natural, the money is not there to buy it, but He talks to me about it.

00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:36.822
He says, "Brandon, that piece of land right there in the next couple of years is going to be worth tens of millions of dollars.

00:33:43.720 --> 00:33:43.942
" I said, "Wow, that's awesome.

00:33:43.942 --> 00:33:44.609
Praise God.

00:33:44.609 --> 00:33:47.169
It's worth a million dollars right now.

00:33:47.169 --> 00:33:54.084
" So I look it up and sure enough, a couple of years later, just like He said, a developer bought it.

00:33:55.720 --> 00:33:59.072
He put houses on it.

00:34:08.710 --> 00:34:09.115
It's worth tens of millions just like the Lord said.

00:34:17.818 --> 00:34:17.969
And I look at those things and I grow.

00:34:25.840 --> 00:34:34.160
It helps me to grow because I realize it helps get that trust level up, because one day He's going to talk and I'm going to have the money and I'm going to buy that land.

00:34:34.160 --> 00:34:40.480
I'm going to do what He said, and you can take it to the bank.

00:34:40.480 --> 00:34:43.896
God will bless your hands.

00:34:43.896 --> 00:34:44.880
Why?

00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:46.880
Because I practice His presence.

00:34:47.093 --> 00:34:51.020
I don't look to Him as a genie in the bottle.

00:34:51.939 --> 00:34:59.840
"Oh God, Holy Ghost, you're like my genie in a little bottle right here.

00:34:59.840 --> 00:35:01.380
My oil.

00:35:01.380 --> 00:35:02.978
Tell me what it is.

00:35:02.978 --> 00:35:12.305
Let me have the lottery numbers, lucky snake eyes 77 or whatever.

00:35:12.305 --> 00:35:13.430
" And you got it.

00:35:22.559 --> 00:35:22.759
"And Lord, we're going to make it.

00:35:26.663 --> 00:35:27.091
" No, it's flaky.

00:35:29.537 --> 00:35:29.914
I look at it.

00:35:34.587 --> 00:35:35.213
I sow the seed.

00:35:36.156 --> 00:35:38.680
I say, "Father, I spend time with you.

00:35:50.411 --> 00:35:50.674
" And in the least expected times and in unlikely ways, He talks.

00:35:50.674 --> 00:36:01.970
I'll be outside in the yard pulling weeds—and I don't have weeds right now because it's winter, but I'd still go outside and even move a rock around, just sitting out there.

00:36:01.970 --> 00:36:03.160
That's what I did today.

00:36:04.585 --> 00:36:09.777
I sit out there and I listen because He'll talk whenever your mind is off of your problems.

00:36:09.777 --> 00:36:13.960
Think about how you can pray for somebody else today.

00:36:13.960 --> 00:36:16.911
Think about how you can maybe pray for your loved ones.

00:36:16.911 --> 00:36:27.473
Like I was praying for my mom and my dad; they're going through hard times.

00:36:27.473 --> 00:36:44.943
You listen to people and you take your eyes off of yourself for a minute and pray for somebody else in their need, and God will speak to you and He'll correct you a lot of the time.

00:36:44.943 --> 00:36:48.057
He'll correct me: "You shouldn't have said that.

00:36:48.057 --> 00:36:50.664
None of your business.

00:36:56.600 --> 00:36:56.925
You don't need to say that.

00:36:57.575 --> 00:37:02.315
" And I wasn't even looking for what He said.

00:37:02.315 --> 00:37:06.290
But He'll talk in the most unlikely way.

00:37:06.290 --> 00:37:09.760
You'll be like, "Well, look at that.

00:37:09.760 --> 00:37:11.520
I wasn't even asking for that.

00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:11.740
But thank you.

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:20.720
" And I don't just cast it aside.

00:37:36.703 --> 00:37:36.977
I listen to it and I take note of it.

00:37:37.251 --> 00:37:48.708
I get my phone out and I use the voice recorder because I look at everything He says as precious.

00:37:48.708 --> 00:37:56.330
No matter if I was looking for the answer or not, I take those times to go, "Thank you, sir.

00:37:56.330 --> 00:37:57.170
Thank you, Father.

00:37:57.170 --> 00:38:00.139
Thank you for taking the time to correct me.

00:38:00.139 --> 00:38:05.430
For you correct those that you love.

00:38:06.220 --> 00:38:15.240
" And Father, you'll teach me how to make the bigger money when I can handle it.

00:38:15.240 --> 00:38:31.660
If I'm not able to handle it and it would destroy me and cost me my marriage or cost me my children, then Father, I thank you that you build the character in me.

00:38:31.660 --> 00:38:52.933
But if I don't have the character to handle it, then Father, I thank you, Lord, that you create in me a clean heart, that I'm able to do what I need to do, and thank you, Lord, that I'm a good steward of what you've given me.

00:39:08.720 --> 00:39:11.133
And you can stretch this dollar until it looks like a rubber band, or the quarter, or whatever you've got.

00:39:11.133 --> 00:39:19.640
But I know that if I can sow my offering into good ground, into your church where you're going—and if your church doesn't have good ground, why are you going there?

00:39:28.022 --> 00:39:28.204
I always check it.

00:39:28.204 --> 00:39:28.933
Check the ground.

00:39:28.933 --> 00:39:29.846
Check the pastors.

00:39:29.846 --> 00:39:31.309
Check it first.

00:39:31.309 --> 00:39:32.853
Tithe and then sow.

00:39:32.853 --> 00:39:40.610
But don't dump your load of seed into something until you at least check the ground to see where you're sowing into.

00:39:41.070 --> 00:39:50.830
And if you start seeing a turnaround and you start seeing increase, then you give a little bit more and you sow a little bit more.

00:39:50.830 --> 00:39:56.448
But then if you see a cankerworm on it, first check your heart.

00:39:56.448 --> 00:39:57.760
Check your marriage.

00:39:57.760 --> 00:40:04.680
Make sure there's no strife, because faith works by love.

00:40:04.680 --> 00:40:06.360
Keep the main thing the main thing.

00:40:06.360 --> 00:40:08.387
Keep the relationship vertical.

00:40:08.387 --> 00:40:16.160
If you go horizontal and look at all this other stuff, it's not always the church's fault.

00:40:16.160 --> 00:40:28.160
You've got to make sure that you're in the right place at the right time doing exactly what He asked you to do and sowing where He tells you to sow, being obedient.

00:40:28.160 --> 00:40:47.627
For instance, I was going to sow my seed for my sacrificial gift this year, and I was going to give it back at Christmas time to the minister, and the Lord said, "No.

00:40:47.627 --> 00:40:48.916
" I said, "Why?

00:40:48.916 --> 00:40:50.942
You don't want me to give it all?

00:40:50.942 --> 00:40:55.970
I'll give it somewhere else because, Lord, I want to bless your ministry.

00:40:55.970 --> 00:40:57.795
Let me do this.

00:40:57.795 --> 00:41:01.840
You don't want me to do that?

00:41:01.840 --> 00:41:02.690
" He said, "Not yet.

00:41:02.690 --> 00:41:08.160
" I said, "But I'd like to get it in there and celebrate at Christmas.

00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:10.973
" Just celebrating You because I'm giving it to You.

00:41:10.973 --> 00:41:14.420
I don't give it to the minister; I give it to Jesus because it's His.

00:41:14.420 --> 00:41:22.000
I don't give it for kudos from the person; I give it to Jesus so He goes, "Well done, Brandon.

00:41:31.178 --> 00:41:31.422
" I don't give it so they'll look and say, "Well, thank you for that extra money, sir.

00:41:31.422 --> 00:41:32.400
I appreciate that.

00:41:32.400 --> 00:41:33.925
Oh, good job, Brandon.

00:41:33.925 --> 00:41:37.890
" I give it so Jesus looks at me and says it was the heart.

00:41:37.890 --> 00:41:45.830
Even if they don't even acknowledge you, I gave it to Him.

00:41:54.880 --> 00:41:55.280
It was His Christmas; it's His birthday.

00:42:04.173 --> 00:42:04.404
I sow into the birthday.

00:42:16.240 --> 00:42:16.570
Let me bless you with a birthday present.

00:42:16.570 --> 00:42:17.230
Why?

00:42:17.230 --> 00:42:22.457
The harvest of souls—that's all He cares about.

00:42:22.457 --> 00:42:25.450
He's the Lord of the harvest.

00:42:25.450 --> 00:42:28.160
So he said to me, "No, don't give it.

00:42:31.577 --> 00:42:31.823
" And I thought, "Oh no, there must be something wrong.

00:42:31.823 --> 00:42:37.860
Am I in control or You?

00:42:37.860 --> 00:42:40.954
When do you want me to give it?

00:42:41.983 --> 00:42:46.954
" "I want you to do it on the 27th.

00:42:46.954 --> 00:42:51.510
" "On the 27th?

00:42:51.520 --> 00:42:52.060
Okay.

00:43:00.040 --> 00:43:00.258
" So I told Diana, "We're holding off on that.

00:43:00.258 --> 00:43:02.560
We're not going to give it at all.

00:43:02.560 --> 00:43:04.440
" She goes, "I don't care, honey.

00:43:04.440 --> 00:43:04.760
We've already talked about that.

00:43:04.760 --> 00:43:05.618
We're going to sow.

00:43:05.618 --> 00:43:07.142
We're believing God for 2026.

00:43:07.142 --> 00:43:09.200
Let's go and get it in the ground.

00:43:09.870 --> 00:43:17.384
The faster it's in the ground, the faster the harvest is.

00:43:32.178 --> 00:43:32.396
" I said, "No, the Lord said wait until the 27th.

00:43:32.396 --> 00:43:35.840
" She goes, "Well, I know you hear the Lord.

00:43:35.840 --> 00:43:36.500
" That's interesting.

00:43:36.500 --> 00:43:38.965
So I waited until I could do it today.

00:43:39.150 --> 00:43:45.740
And I was so excited about it because I told the Lord, "I'm giving it for my 2026 increase.

00:43:45.740 --> 00:43:50.569
I'm believing for my 2026 increase.

00:43:50.569 --> 00:44:06.800
I'm believing for our ministry to not have any lack, not anything, and that whatever you tell us to do to grow our ministry in 2026, we're going to have more than enough.

00:44:06.800 --> 00:44:11.800
" So I sow it.

00:44:28.444 --> 00:44:28.689
I went today and I got to put it in there.

00:44:37.657 --> 00:44:38.023
And I felt the anointing all over it.

00:44:57.960 --> 00:44:58.293
And I pray over it just like we always do.

00:44:58.293 --> 00:45:03.000
Anoint it with oil, pray over it, take communion, release it by faith.

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:20.280
We take it as a family, all laying hands on it, praying over the envelope as we put it in the mailbox to go and deliver it because I want it.

00:45:20.280 --> 00:45:25.551
David didn't give anything that didn't cost him something.

00:45:25.551 --> 00:45:28.109
Everything David gave, it cost him something.

00:45:33.315 --> 00:45:45.040
He even talked about it because they were going to give the sacrifice and he said, "No, no, no.

00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.480
It has to cost me something.

00:45:58.240 --> 00:45:58.520
I'm only going to give something that cost me something.

00:45:58.520 --> 00:46:01.154
" So it makes your flesh squirm.

00:46:01.154 --> 00:46:05.920
When it makes your flesh squirm, it's uncomfortable.

00:46:14.293 --> 00:46:14.560
And that's what we do.

00:46:17.960 --> 00:46:18.931
And we do it every year.

00:46:24.333 --> 00:46:24.489
Some years I go, "Oh God, I thank you for this.

00:46:24.489 --> 00:46:25.400
" God loves a cheerful giver.

00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:32.960
So you help out the people that God tells you to.

00:46:32.960 --> 00:46:39.440
That's why I always say it's easy for me to come at you and say all this because we never ask for anything.

00:46:39.440 --> 00:46:44.130
I'm telling you this out of instruction so you can learn.

00:46:53.520 --> 00:46:53.640
And you say, "Brandon, it's about your ministry.

00:46:53.640 --> 00:46:53.880
" No.

00:46:53.880 --> 00:47:09.272
I'm not teaching you this to sow to me; I'm teaching this so that you'll learn how to grow in your ministry and what God's called you to do.

00:47:09.272 --> 00:47:10.456
Do you understand?

00:47:21.693 --> 00:47:22.040
I hate manipulation, especially in churches and big ministries.

00:47:22.040 --> 00:47:27.009
There is a lot of manipulation, especially in the Word of Faith circles.

00:47:29.800 --> 00:47:35.754
I look at it and say you can keep it and use it for whatever the Lord tells you to do.

00:47:35.754 --> 00:47:40.870
I don't think a preacher should ever be manipulating people.

00:47:49.269 --> 00:47:54.390
It's wrong, especially using the platform.

00:47:54.390 --> 00:48:01.276
Follow the Holy Ghost and do what He tells you to do.

00:48:01.276 --> 00:48:05.960
Mary said, "Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:48:05.960 --> 00:48:06.611
" Obey.

00:48:06.611 --> 00:48:16.291
Fill the water pots with water, and He turned the water into wine.

00:48:16.291 --> 00:48:20.940
Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:48:20.940 --> 00:48:27.840
Don't listen to the man of God tugging at your heart with emotional violins.

00:48:27.840 --> 00:48:30.240
"Won't you help me?

00:48:30.240 --> 00:48:31.931
" No, keep your money.

00:48:31.931 --> 00:48:35.920
Follow the voice of God for your life.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
I do not like spiritual manipulation.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
I've seen it done; I worked for some big ministries.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
Don't do this.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Don't give out of emotion ever.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Give when the Holy Spirit tugs at you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Be spirit-led in your giving.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Listen to the voice of the Spirit of the Lord concerning this.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
There are too many high notes on the organ and you say, "I feel the Holy Ghost.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
" No, you didn't feel anything.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
This isn't the Holy Ghost; it's flesh, and you're being flaky.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
I'm not going to be giving out of flakiness.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I don't care how much you think you need for your orphanage or your project.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.800
You want to play a high note on a key on your organ to make me feel like I'm feeling the Holy Ghost, and you play the tambourine.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Sit down.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
It's flaky.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
You're all excited and people are falling out.

